               <head>Persian translation of Sufi work, Sharh ul-Ghausiyyah</head>
               <msContents>
                  <summary>1 copy of a work by Valī ibn Mulūk Shāh al-Ṣiddīqī al-Qādirī</summary>
                  <msItem class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2010109193 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2008112367 https://lccn.loc.gov/n90650670 " n="1" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_967B-item1">
                     <author>
                        <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" type="supplied" key="person_f7636">Valī ibn Mulūk Shāh al-Ṣiddīqī al-Qādirī</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="per" type="supplied" key="person_f7636">ولى ابن ملوك شاه الصّدّيقى القادرى </persName>
                     </author>
                     <note>
                        <p>Excerpt paraphrasing and expanding in Persian the Arabic treatise on the principles of mysticism, ascribed to <persName key="viaf_71359982" role="ant">Shaykh ʿAbd al-Qādir al-Jīlānī</persName> (d. 561/1166), by the translator <persName key="person_f7636" role="trl aut">Valī ibn Mulūk Shāh al-Ṣiddīqī al-Qādirī</persName>, author of another work on mysticism, <title>Naṣīḥat al-ʿārifīn</title>.
                        </p>
                        <p>Although the work lacks its formal title, it has been labelled <title>Sharḥ-i Ghaws̲īyah</title> in the colophon. 
                        </p>
                        <p>Defective at beginning. 
</p>
                        <p>Fine rounded Central Asian naskh with full vocalisation for Arabic quotations. 
</p>
                        <p>The work is bound, but lacking its original covers; water and fungal stains. 
</p>
                        <p>Dated colophon (f. 43v): 4 Z̲ī al-Qaʿdah [10]87/8 January 1677. </p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="per">Persian </textLang>
                     <note/>
                  </msItem>
